components.label: Location name
components.tooltip: Your location name is what you go by mainly when referring to your specific location. This is used to identify and differentiate your location from other locations within your institution.

components.label: Institution code
components.tooltip: Unique 4 digit alpha code that is assigned the first time this location is designated in Canada.

components.label: HTML
components.content: Name someone who can be your main contact for your location. This may be yourself or someone similar.
